# Prompt Improvement Formats

## By Style/Tone
- `improve this prompt-concise: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-formal: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-conversational: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-technical: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-academic: "..."`

## By Structure
- `improve this prompt-step-by-step: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-with-examples: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-bullet-format: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-structured: "..."`

## By Purpose
- `improve this prompt-clarity: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-specificity: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-completeness: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-effectiveness: "..."`

## By Output Control
- `improve this prompt-detailed-output: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-brief-output: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-format-controlled: "..."`

## Combination Formats
- `improve this prompt-concise+examples: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-formal+structured: "..."`
- `improve this prompt-technical+step-by-step: "..."`

## Key Insight
The most universally effective improvements tend to be **"concise"** (removes fluff, sharpens focus), **"specific"** (adds concrete details), and **"structured"** (organizes for clarity). These work well alone or combined with other modifiers based on your specific needs.